1.quote_content: The hallmark of a real man is controlling himself, controlling his emotions, and acting appropriately regardless of how he feels.
1.author: Andrew Tate

2.quote_content: Depression is not real. Feeling depressed is real. So, you can feel depressed, but you feel depressed and that is a natural, biological, evolutionary trigger for you to change something in your life.
2.author: Andrew Tate

3.quote_content: The only way to get rid of a negative thought is to replace it with a positive one.
3.author: Andrew Tate

5.quote_content: Don't being a brokie, do some pushups and grind
5.author: Andrew Tate

6.quote_content: You only have one life, don't waste it.
6.author: Andrew Tate

7.quote_content: Success is not final, failure is not fatal: it is the courage to continue that counts.
7.author: Winston Churchill

8.quote_content: Believe you can and you're halfway there.
8.author: Theodore Roosevelt

9.quote_content: Be the change you wish to see in the world.
9.author: Mahatma Gandhi

10.quote_content: You miss 100 % of the shots you don't take.
10.author: Wayne Gretzky

11.quote_content: Successful people do what unsuccessful people are not willing to do. Don't wish it were easier; wish you were better.
11.author: Jim Rohn

12.quote_content: The only place where success comes before work is in the dictionary.
12.author: Vidal Sassoon

13.quote_content: The only person you are destined to become is the person you decide to be.
13.author: Ralph Waldo Emerson

14.quote_content: The best revenge is massive success.
14.author: Frank Sinatra

15.quote_content: The harder you work for something, the greater you'll feel when you achieve it.
15.author: George Sheehan

16.quote_content: The only way to do great work is to love what you do. If you haven't found it yet, keep looking. Don't settle.
16.author: Steve Jobs

17.quote_content: Success is not how high you have climbed, but how you make a positive difference to the world.
17.author: Roy T. Bennett

18.quote_content: It's not the years in your life that count. It's the life in your years.
18.author: Abraham Lincoln

19.quote_content: Happiness is not something ready made. It comes from your own actions.
19.author: Dalai Lama

20.quote_content: Don't let yesterday take up too much of today.
20.author: Will Rogers

21.quote_content: You learn more from failure than from success. Don't let it stop you. Failure builds character.
21.author: Unknown

22.quote_content: Your only limit is the one you set for yourself.
22.author: Miguel Cervantes

23.quote_content: No one can make you feel inferior without your consent.
23.author: Eleanor Roosevelt

24.quote_content: Believe in yourself and all that you are. Know that there is something inside you that is greater than any obstacle.
24.author: Christian D. Larson

25.quote_content: It's not what you achieve, it's what you overcome. That's what defines your career.
25.author: Carlton Fisk

26.quote_content: Don't wait for opportunities, create them.
26.author: Charles R. Swindoll

27.quote_content: Take the risk or lose the chance.
27.author: Unknown

28.quote_content: The best revenge is massive success.
28.author: Frank Sinatra
